From: Douglas Edmunds [mailto:dedmunds@au1.ibm.com] On Behalf Of Optus Space Support
Sent: Sunday, 25 May 2008 10:19 PM
To: Command Centre
Subject: SPACE Sev1 update


Julian, 

Regarding the SPACE Sev1: 

Approx 3pm, logged on, checked server logs, some error messages: 'Server failed' 
Suggested application server restart as the quickest way to resolve, as shutdown process kills all threads and starts cleanly. 
Wasfy approved, raised severity, restarted app server (3.35-3.45). 
Continued to investigate log, some database errors (ORA-01001: invalid cursor), as well as some app errors caused by null pointer exceptions and unsatisfied tuples. 

Problem still occurred , concall with Wasfy, users, and Ceasar. Users explained problems, and gave example cases (SPACE 3529885,3529932,3529658) 

Problem 1: Space 'Server Failed' error when attempting to bring up application, search returns result, but unable to load, (also edit same prob?) 
Problem 2: Tuxedo errors in Focus when attempting re-collect 

I was able to replicate Server Failed on app 3529885, investigated (amongst other things) the following: 
ran daily extract to try and identify data pattern and identify missing data, checked all apps from same dealer, all fine, checked all unsat tup errors, all fine, checked Focus (SBLS/Siebel) submission, looks ok. 

Comparatively few errors since restart, but could be due to decrease in load, will monitor closely tomorrow and engage SME. 

-- 

Regards 

Doug 
SPACE Support
